INSERT INTO `programs` VALUES (1,'2025-03-26 11:42:01.947055','2025-04-01 15:41:19.000000',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,2,0,'MUGGA WILD WATER RAFTING','Experience the Thrill of White Water Rafting in East Africa!\n\nAt Mugga Tours, we invite adventure seekers to embark on an exhilarating white water rafting experience across some of the most stunning rivers in East Africa. Whether you’re a seasoned rafter or a first-timer, our white water rafting package promises an unforgettable adventure filled with excitement, breathtaking landscapes, and a touch of adrenaline.\n\nPackage Highlights:\n\n1. Destinations:\n   - **Nile River, Jinja (Uganda):** Known as the adventure capital of East Africa, Jinja offers world-class white water rafting. Experience Grade 5 rapids, where you can navigate through thrilling drops and turbulent waters, all while surrounded by lush green landscapes.\n   - **Tana River (Kenya):** Enjoy a more serene experience while tackling moderate rapids, ideal for both beginners and families. This river combines scenic beauty with fun-filled adventure.\n   - **Murchison Falls (Uganda):** Rafting here is unique, as you’ll experience the incredible sight of the Nile crashing through the Murchison Falls. The combination of rugged terrain and thrilling rapids makes for an unforgettable journey.\n\n2. **Itinerary Overview:**\n   - **Day 1: Arrival and Orientation**\n     - Arrive in Jinja or your chosen destination.\n     - Enjoy a welcome briefing from our experienced guides who will provide safety instructions and rafting techniques.\n     - Gear up with safety equipment and get ready for an adventure of a lifetime!\n\n   - **Day 2: Rafting Adventure**\n     - Set off on an exhilarating rafting journey. Navigate through breathtaking rapids, enjoy the thrill of plunging down waves, and take in the stunning scenery.\n     - Stop for a riverside picnic lunch, where you can relax and enjoy the beauty of nature.\n     - Continue your rafting adventure, with opportunities for swimming in calmer sections of the river.\n\n   - **Day 3: Return and Reflection**\n     - After an action-packed day, return to base for a hot meal and a chance to share stories and experiences with fellow adventurers.\n     - Optional activities such as zip-lining or visiting local attractions can be arranged for those interested in more adventure or cultural experiences.\n\n3. **Inclusions:**\n   - Professional guide services with extensive experience in white water rafting.\n   - All necessary safety gear including helmets, life jackets, and paddles.\n   - Meals during the rafting day, including a hearty riverside picnic.\n   - Transportation to and from the rafting site.\n   - Accommodation options available upon request for those wishing to extend their stay.\n\n4. **Safety First:**\n   - Safety is our top priority. Our guides are trained in swift water rescue and first aid, ensuring that you are in safe hands throughout your adventure. We adhere to the highest safety standards to guarantee a thrilling yet secure experience.\n\n5. **Perfect for Everyone:**\n   - Our white water rafting package is suitable for individuals, families, and groups. Customized itineraries are available to cater to different skill levels and preferences.\n\n#### **Book Your Adventure Today!**\n\nJoin Mugga Tours for an exhilarating white water rafting experience that combines adventure, nature, and cultural immersion in East Africa. Whether you’re seeking a heart-pounding thrill or a family-friendly adventure, our white water rafting package promises to deliver lasting memories. \n\nContact us today to learn more about our white water rafting packages and to begin your journey into the wild beauty of East Africa!','Full day rafting',1.00,'Mon,Tue,Wed,Thur,Fri,Sat,Sun','https://res.cloudinary.com/dgjtaqrhg/image/upload/v1742989302/IMG_0181_g3ja4j.jpg',1,20,'activity'),(2,'2025-03-26 13:29:55.907153','2025-04-01 15:41:49.000000',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,2,0,'MUGGA TOURS YOUR GATE WAY TO MURCHISION FALLS NATIONAL PARK ','\nDiscover Murchison Falls, Uganda: An Unforgettable Destination\n\nMurchison Falls National Park, located in northwestern Uganda, is one of the country\'s most spectacular natural wonders and a premier destination for safari enthusiasts. This stunning park is known for its dramatic landscapes, diverse wildlife, and the magnificent Murchison Falls itself, where the Nile River squeezes through a narrow gorge and plunges over 40 meters, creating a breathtaking spectacle.\n\nWhy Visit Murchison Falls?\n\n1. Breathtaking Waterfalls:\n   - The iconic Murchison Falls is the centerpiece of the park. Witness the power and beauty of the Nile as it surges through a rocky cleft, producing a thunderous roar and a spectacular mist that creates rainbows on sunny days. Hiking to the top of the falls provides panoramic views and great photo opportunities.\n\n2. Rich Wildlife:\n   - Murchison Falls is home to a rich array of wildlife, including:\n     - Big Five: Spot elephants, lions, leopards, buffaloes, and rhinos in their natural habitats.\n     - Unique Species: Look for rare species such as the Uganda kob, oribi, and various primates.\n     - Bird Watching: The park is a birding paradise with over 450 species, including the rare shoebill stork, which can often be seen in the wetlands.\n\n3. Game Drives and Boat Safaris:\n   - Game Drives: Explore the park’s vast savannahs and watch for herds of elephants, giraffes, and various antelope species during early morning or late afternoon game drives.\n   - Boat Safaris: Take a relaxing boat cruise on the Nile River to the base of the falls. This experience not only allows you to see wildlife along the riverbanks but also provides close encounters with hippos, crocodiles, and a plethora of birds.\n\n4. Cultural Experiences:\n   - Engage with local communities around the park. Learn about their cultures, traditions, and ways of life. You can participate in guided cultural tours to villages and experience traditional dance, music, and crafts.\n\n5. Adventure Activities:\n   - In addition to wildlife viewing, Murchison Falls offers adventure activities such as:\n     - White Water Rafting: Experience thrilling rapids on the Nile River.\n     - Hiking: Explore various trails for different levels of hiking enthusiasts, offering scenic views and opportunities to encounter wildlife.\n\nAccommodation Options:\n\nMurchison Falls National Park offers a range of accommodation choices to cater to different preferences and budgets:\n\n- Luxury Lodges: Experience comfort and luxury at lodges that provide stunning views and excellent amenities.\n- Mid-Range Options: Enjoy comfortable accommodations with good service and proximity to the park\'s attractions.\n- Camping Sites: For those seeking a more rustic experience, campsites are available, allowing you to immerse yourself in nature.\n\n Book with Mugga Tours for a hassle-free experience, where transportation and itineraries are handled by experienced guides.\n\nConclusion:\n\nMurchison Falls is a must-visit destination for anyone traveling to Uganda. With its stunning landscapes, rich wildlife, and thrilling adventure opportunities, it promises an unforgettable safari experience. Whether you’re exploring the falls, embarking on a game drive, or enjoying a boat safari, Murchison Falls National Park is sure to leave you with lasting memories. \n\nContact Mugga Tours today to customize your Murchison Falls adventure and discover the beauty of Uganda!','FULL DAY',1000.00,'Mon,Tue,Wed,Thur,Fri,Sat,Sun','https://res.cloudinary.com/dgjtaqrhg/image/upload/v1742995784/IMG_0032_rdelck.jpg',1,20,'destination'),(3,'2025-03-26 13:46:58.693038','2025-04-02 09:58:02.000000',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,3,0,'MUGGA TOURS BRINGS YOU CLOSE TO WITNESS THE GREAT MIGRATION MAGIC IN MASAI MARA THIS SUMMER ','Experience the Wonders of Masai Mara Game Reserve\n\nThe Masai Mara Game Reserve, located in southwestern Kenya, is renowned for its extraordinary wildlife and stunning landscapes. This UNESCO World Heritage site is a must-visit for any safari enthusiast, offering an unforgettable experience of trekking and observing some of Africa\'s most iconic animals in their natural habitats.\n\nWhy Choose Masai Mara for Your Safari?\n\n1. Diverse Wildlife:\n   - The Masai Mara is home to an incredible variety of wildlife, including the famous \"Big Five\": lions, leopards, elephants, buffaloes, and rhinoceroses. \n   - Witness the Great Migration (usually between July and October), where millions of wildebeests and zebras migrate across the plains in search of fresh grazing grounds, creating a breathtaking spectacle.\n\n2. Trekking Adventures:\n   - Lion Trekking: Join expert guides on a thrilling trek to track and observe lions in their natural habitat. Experience the thrill of watching these magnificent predators in action, whether they are lounging in the shade or hunting for their next meal.\n   - Cheetah and Leopard Tracking: Experience the grace and speed of cheetahs as you trek through the savannah. Observe leopards as they stealthily navigate their environment, often spotted resting on tree branches or hidden in the tall grass.\n   - Wild Dog Expeditions: The endangered African wild dog can also be found in the Masai Mara. Trek with our knowledgeable guides to locate and observe these fascinating pack hunters in their territory.\n\n3. Unique Ecosystem:\n   - The Masai Mara features diverse ecosystems, including rolling savannahs, acacia woodlands, and riverine forests. This variety supports a rich array of wildlife and bird species, making each trekking experience unique and exciting.\n   - Birdwatching enthusiasts will delight in spotting over 470 species, including the striking African fish eagle and the vibrant lilac-breasted roller.\n\n4. Cultural Encounters:\n   - Engage with the local Masai communities, known for their vibrant culture and traditions. Participate in cultural experiences such as traditional dances, storytelling, and visits to local homesteads to learn about their way of life.\n\n5. Accommodation Options:\n   - Luxury Camps: Enjoy the comfort of luxury tented camps that offer stunning views of the Mara plains, gourmet meals, and exceptional service.\n   - Mid-Range Lodges: Experience comfortable lodges that provide easy access to game viewing areas, allowing you to relax after a day of adventure.\n   - Budget Options: For those seeking a more economical choice, budget camps are available, providing essential amenities for a memorable safari experience.\nConclusion:\n\nThe Masai Mara Game Reserve offers a remarkable experience for wildlife lovers and adventure seekers alike. With its stunning landscapes, diverse wildlife, and thrilling trekking opportunities, a safari in the Masai Mara is sure to be a highlight of your East African journey. \n\nContact Mugga Tours today to plan your unforgettable trekking adventure in the Masai Mara and immerse yourself in the magic of the African wilderness!','3 DAYS',1.00,'Mon,Tue,Wed,Thur,Fri,Sat,Sun','https://res.cloudinary.com/dgjtaqrhg/image/upload/v1743587876/giraffe_mama_and_baby_1_t3vygs.jpg',1,20,'destination'),(4,'2025-03-31 17:19:10.403998','2025-03-31 17:32:04.000000','2025-03-31 17:32:04.000000',NULL,NULL,NULL,2,0,'Sample pkg','Sample pkg','12 weeks',1200.00,'Mon, Tue, Wed,Thur','https://res.cloudinary.com/dgjtaqrhg/image/upload/v1743441547/19025245_836791243140888_7540301803216175463_o_udjows.jpg',1,20,'activity'),(5,'2025-04-01 12:08:46.873800','2025-04-01 12:08:52.000000','2025-04-01 12:08:52.000000',NULL,NULL,NULL,2,0,'rugyf8i','gggggggggggggggggg','htnjfy',1.00,'fjjjhj','https://res.cloudinary.com/dgjtaqrhg/image/upload/v1743509295/2025_02_19_11_26_IMG_9533_ot6jh1.heic',1,20,'activity'),(6,'2025-04-02 07:16:42.316751','2025-04-02 07:16:42.316751',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,0,'MUGGA TOURS WELCOMES YOU TO NYUNGWE FOREST NATIONAL PARK WHERE  ADVENTURE BEGINS ','Nyungwe Forest National Park: A Haven of Biodiversity\n\nLocated in southwestern Rwanda, Nyungwe Forest National Park is a stunning example of Africa\'s ancient forests. This breathtaking destination is home to:\n- Diverse wildlife: Over 300 species of birds, 75 species of mammals, and 13 species of primates, including chimpanzees and colobus monkeys.\n- Lush vegetation: A canopy of towering trees, colorful flowers, and vibrant foliage.\n- Sparkling waterfalls: The Kamiranzovu Waterfall and other scenic falls.\n- Canopy walkway and hanging bridge: Take a thrilling walk above the forest canopy on the 200-meter-long hanging bridge, offering breathtaking views.\n- Guided hikes: Venture into the forest with expert guides, spotting wildlife and learning about the ecosystem.\n- Chimpanzee trekking: Track and observe chimpanzees in their natural habitat.\n- Birdwatching: Discover the park\'s incredible avifauna, with over 300 species.\n- Cultural experiences: Visit local communities and learn about their traditional ways of life.\n\nJoin Mugga Tours for an unforgettable Nyungwe Forest adventure!','FULL DAY',1.00,'Mon,Tue,Wed,Thur,Fri,Sat,Sun','https://res.cloudinary.com/dgjtaqrhg/image/upload/v1743577353/nyungwe_forest_fqbak1.webp',1,20,'destination'),(7,'2025-04-02 07:47:38.865580','2025-04-02 07:47:38.865580',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,0,'A GATE AWAY TO THE VIRUNGA NATIONAL  PARK WITH MUGGA TOURS','Mugga Tours\' Virunga National Park adventure!\n\nLocated in Northern Rwanda, Virunga National Park is a UNESCO World Heritage Site and one of Africa\'s most incredible conservation areas. This breathtaking destination is home to:\n\n- Mountain gorillas and other primates, \n- Volcanic landscapes (Virunga ranges) Mountain Bisoke, Sabinyo and others,\n- Diverse wildlife and \n- Lake Kivu\n\nExplore Virunga National Park with Mugga Tours\n\n- Gorilla trekking: Venture into the forest with expert guides to track and observe mountain gorillas.\n- Volcano hikes: Climb Mount Nyiragongo or Mount Nyamuragira for breathtaking views.\n- Wildlife spotting: Go on guided game drives or walks to spot the park\'s diverse wildlife.\n- Community visits: Learn about local cultures and traditions during community visits.\n\nJoin Mugga Tours for an unforgettable Virunga National Park adventure!','Full day',1.00,'Mon, Tue, Wed, Thur, Fri, Sat, Sun','https://res.cloudinary.com/dgjtaqrhg/image/upload/v1743579121/Virunga-National-parc-Landscape-picture-by-Therese-R-1400x928_evdcos.jpg',1,20,'destination'),(8,'2025-04-02 08:30:07.164021','2025-04-02 09:05:05.000000',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,4,0,'Queen Elizabeth National Park: Unleash the Adventure with Mugga Tours','Queen Elizabeth National Park: Uganda\'s Premier Wildlife Destination\n\nLocated in southwestern Uganda, Queen Elizabeth National Park is a UNESCO Biosphere Reserve and one of Africa\'s most renowned conservation areas. This breathtaking destination boasts;\n- Diverse wildlife: \n- Kazinga Channel:\n- Ishasha Sector: \n- Kyambura Gorge: and many more\n\nExplore Queen Elizabeth National Park with Mugga Tours','1 day',1.00,'Mon,Tue,Wed,Thur,Fri,Sat,Sun','https://res.cloudinary.com/dgjtaqrhg/image/upload/v1743584695/IMG_9637_cropped_1_z8eyoh.jpg',1,20,'destination'),(9,'2025-04-02 08:59:10.229076','2025-04-02 09:01:02.000000','2025-04-02 09:01:02.000000',NULL,NULL,NULL,2,0,'tyhgj,ccccccccccg',',ticyghjytrdfghjfdyukcvb','full day',1.00,'mon','https://res.cloudinary.com/dgjtaqrhg/image/upload/v1743584312/Untitled_design_rdxs44.png',1,20,'destination'),(10,'2025-04-02 09:24:20.003849','2025-04-02 09:32:48.000000',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,4,0,'MUGGA TOURS PRESNTS THE WORLD\'S MOST UNIQUE URBAN PARK ','Nairobi National Park: The Ultimate Urban Wildlife Experience\n\n This incredible park boasts:\n- Over 400 species of birds, lions, leopards, rhinos, giraffes, and many more.\n- Scenic landscapes\n- Conservation efforts: A sanctuary for endangered black rhinos and a hub for wildlife research and conservation.\n- Game drives: \n- Walking safaris: \n- Birdwatching: \n\nTag along with Mugga Tours for an unforgettable Nairobi National Park adventure!','Full Day',1.00,'Mon,Tue,Wed,Thur,Fri,Sat,Sun','https://res.cloudinary.com/dgjtaqrhg/image/upload/v1743586363/nai_lion_y6a7gk.jpg',1,20,'destination'),(11,'2025-04-02 10:32:11.379443','2025-04-02 10:34:00.000000',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,2,0,'Serengeti National Park: Endless Plains of Wonders','Serengeti National Park: Endless Plains of Wonder\n\nLocated in Tanzania, Serengeti National Park is a world-renowned destination and one of Africa\'s most iconic wildlife reserves. This incredible park boasts:\n\n- Endless plains: Stretching as far as the eye can see, the Serengeti\'s rolling grasslands are home to an incredible array of wildlife.\n- The Great Migration: Witness the majestic spectacle of millions of wildebeest, zebras, and gazelles migrating across the plains in search of greener pastures.\n- Diverse wildlife: Lions, leopards, elephants, giraffes, and many more species call the Serengeti home.\n- Stunning landscapes: From the granite outcrops of the Moru Kopjes to the majestic acacia trees, the Serengeti\'s scenery is breathtaking.\n\n- Game drives: Venture into the park with expert guides to spot the diverse wildlife.\n- Sunrise and sunset safaris: Witness the park\'s stunning landscapes and wildlife during the golden hours.\n- Hot air balloon safaris: Take a bird\'s-eye view of the Serengeti\'s endless plains and wildlife.\n- Cultural experiences: Learn about the Maasai people\'s traditions and way of life.\n\nJoin Mugga Tours for an unforgettable Serengeti National Park adventure this summer. ','3 days',1.00,'Mon,Tue,Wed,Thur,Fri,Sat,Sun','https://res.cloudinary.com/dgjtaqrhg/image/upload/v1743589909/serengeti2_tgjfbs.jpg',1,20,'destination'),(12,'2025-04-03 08:44:02.389833','2025-04-03 08:44:02.389833',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,0,'DESCEND INTO THE WILD  FOR AN UNFORGETTABLE NGORONGORO EXPERIENCE  WITH MUGGA TOURS ',' Unparalleled Wildlife Adventure with Mugga Tours.\n\nDiscover:\n\nThe World\'s Largest Caldera: Explore the breathtaking Ngorongoro Crater, a natural wonder teeming with wildlife.\nDiverse Wildlife: Encounter the Big Five – lions, elephants, buffalo, leopards, and rhinos – alongside hyenas, cheetahs, and numerous bird species.\nUnique Landscapes: Marvel at the crater\'s majestic walls, sparkling lakes, and lush forests.\n\nExperience with Mugga Tours:\n\n Guided Safaris: Expert guides lead you through the crater\'s stunning landscapes and wildlife hotspots.\n Cultural Encounters: Visit nearby Maasai communities and learn about their traditional ways of life.\n Unparalleled Scenic Views: Witness the sunrise or sunset over the crater for an unforgettable experience.\n\nBook your Ngorongoro adventure with Mugga Tours today!','FULL DAY',1.00,'Mon,Tue,Wed,Thur,Fri,Sat,Sun','https://res.cloudinary.com/dgjtaqrhg/image/upload/v1743669835/ngorongoro-crater-floor-teaming-with-game_dk53zo.jpg',1,20,'destination'),(13,'2025-04-03 11:35:54.316972','2025-04-03 11:35:54.316972',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,0,'GORILLA TREKING WITH MUGGA TOURS','1. Gorilla trekking: Embark on a once-in-a-lifetime journey to track majestic mountain gorillas in Uganda\'s Bwindi Impenetrable National Park or Rwanda\'s Volcanoes National Park.\n\n    - Book with Mugga Tours: Our expert guides will lead you through the dense forest, ensuring a safe and unforgettable encounter with these incredible creatures.\n    - Exciting fact: Mountain gorillas are one of the most endangered species in the world, with only around 1,000 individuals remaining in the wild.','FULL DAY',1.00,'Mon,Tue,Wed,Thur,Fri,Sat,Sun','https://res.cloudinary.com/dgjtaqrhg/image/upload/v1743678059/close-up-beautiful-gorilla-wild_ncscqp.jpg',1,20,'activity'),(14,'2025-04-03 12:06:43.921672','2025-04-03 12:06:43.921672',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,0,'BUNGEE JUMPING','1. Bungee jumping: Take the ultimate leap of faith off the Victoria Falls Bridge in Uganda, experiencing an unforgettable rush as you freefall 100 meters towards the Zambezi River.\n\n    - Book with Mugga Tours: Experience the thrill of bungee jumping with our expert guides and safety equipment.\n    - Exciting fact: The Victoria Falls Bridge is one of the highest commercial bungee jumping sites in the world.','FULL DAY',1.00,'Mon,Tue,Wed,Thur,Fri,Sat,Sun','https://res.cloudinary.com/dgjtaqrhg/image/upload/v1743681997/wp9383396-bungee-jumping-wallpapers_xsrpnr.jpg',1,20,'activity'),(15,'2025-04-03 12:17:57.682231','2025-04-03 12:17:57.682231',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,0,'SKY DIVING WITH MUGGA TOURS','2. Skydiving: Soar above Tanzania\'s breathtaking landscapes, taking in the stunning views of Mount Kilimanjaro, the Serengeti, or the Indian Ocean coast.\n\n    - Book with Mugga Tours: Join our experienced skydiving instructors for an unforgettable jump over Tanzania\'s stunning landscapes.\n    - Exciting fact: Skydiving in Tanzania offers a unique perspective on the country\'s diverse landscapes and wildlife.','FULL DAY',1.00,'Mon,Tue,Wed,Thur,Fri,Sat,Sun','https://res.cloudinary.com/dgjtaqrhg/image/upload/v1743682669/wp2025638-skydive-wallpapers_j72fin.jpg',1,20,'activity'),(16,'2025-04-03 12:19:24.161595','2025-04-03 12:19:24.161595',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,0,'ROCK CLIMBING WITH MUGGA','3. Rock climbing: Scale the rugged cliffs of Mount Kenya, Uganda\'s Mount Elgon, or Tanzania\'s Mount Meru, challenging yourself physically and mentally.\n\n    - Book with Mugga Tours: Our expert rock climbing guides will lead you through the challenging terrain, ensuring a safe and exhilarating experience.\n    - Exciting fact: Mount Kenya is the second-highest peak in Africa and offers some of the most challenging and rewarding rock climbing routes on the continent.','FULL DAY',1.00,'Mon,Tue,Wed,Thur,Fri,Sat,Sun','https://res.cloudinary.com/dgjtaqrhg/image/upload/v1743682758/wp14676314-rock-climbing-adventure-wallpapers_jraaep.jpg',1,20,'activity'),(17,'2025-04-03 12:35:40.572552','2025-04-03 12:35:40.572552',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,0,'ZIP LINING','4. Zip lining: Fly through the treetops of Uganda\'s Mabira Forest or Kenya\'s Aberdare Forest, reaching speeds of up to 100 km/h.\n\n    - Book with Mugga Tours: Experience the thrill of zip lining with our expert guides and safety equipment, taking in the stunning views of the forest canopy.\n    - Exciting fact: The Mabira Forest is home to over 300 species of birds and offers a unique perspective on the forest ecosystem.','FULL DAY',1.00,'Mon,Tue,Wed,Thur,Fri,Sat,Sun','https://res.cloudinary.com/dgjtaqrhg/image/upload/v1743683725/wp4851423-zipline-wallpapers_zexd0n.jpg',1,20,'activity'),(18,'2025-04-03 12:56:38.594534','2025-04-03 12:56:38.594534',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,0,'GAME DRIVES','3. Game drives: Explore the iconic savannas and grasslands of Kenya\'s Maasai Mara National Reserve, Tanzania\'s Serengeti National Park, or Uganda\'s Queen Elizabeth National Park.\n\n    - Book with Mugga Tours: Our expert guides will lead you on an unforgettable journey through the African wilderness, spotting incredible wildlife and taking in the stunning scenery.\n    - Exciting fact: The Maasai Mara National Reserve is home to the Big Five (lion, leopard, rhinoceros, elephant, and Cape buffalo) and offers some of the most spectacular game viewing in Africa.','FULL DAY',1.00,'Mon,Tue,Wed,Thur,Fri,Sat,Sun','https://res.cloudinary.com/dgjtaqrhg/image/upload/v1743684989/MUGGA_Wallpaper_PNG_2_q96alm.png',1,20,'activity'),(19,'2025-04-03 13:02:39.639616','2025-04-03 13:02:39.639616',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,0,'BIRD WATCHING','4. Bird watching: Spot over 1,000 species of birds in Uganda\'s Murchison Falls National Park or Kenya\'s Lake Nakuru National Park, a paradise for ornithologists.\n\n    - Book with Mugga Tours: Join our expert birding guides for an unforgettable journey through the African wilderness, spotting incredible bird species and taking in the stunning scenery.\n    - Exciting fact: Uganda\'s Murchison Falls National Park is home to over 450 species of birds, including the iconic shoebill stork.','FULL DAY',1.00,'Mon,Tue,Wed,Thur,Fri,Sat,Sun','https://res.cloudinary.com/dgjtaqrhg/image/upload/v1743685317/MUGGA_Wallpaper_PNG_3_xgoav7.png',1,20,'activity'),(20,'2025-04-03 13:32:26.496615','2025-04-03 13:34:12.000000',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,2,0,'MASAI VILLAGE TOUR','1. Maasai Village Visit: Immerse yourself in traditional Maasai culture, learning about their customs and way of life in Kenya or Tanzania.\n    - Book with Mugga Tours: Visit an authentic Maasai village, interacting with locals and gaining insight into their daily lives.\n    - Exciting fact: The Maasai people are known for their vibrant traditional clothing and intricate beadwork.','FULL DAY',1.00,'Mon,Tue,Wed,Thur,Fri,Sat,Sun','https://res.cloudinary.com/dgjtaqrhg/image/upload/v1743687234/MUGGA_Wallpaper_PNG_4_ii2pah.png',1,20,'activity'),(21,'2025-04-03 13:35:14.321296','2025-04-03 13:35:14.321296',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,0,'COFFEE ROASTING ','2. Coffee Farm Tour: Discover the coffee-making process, from bean to cup, at a local farm in Kenya or Tanzania.\n    - Book with Mugga Tours: Learn about sustainable coffee farming practices and sample some of the world\'s best coffee.\n    - Exciting fact: Kenya is renowned for producing some of the world\'s highest-quality coffee beans.','FULL DAY',1.00,'Mon,Tue,Wed,Thur,Fri,Sat,Sun','https://res.cloudinary.com/dgjtaqrhg/image/upload/v1743687309/Coffee-2_go9fsq.jpg',1,20,'activity'),(22,'2025-04-03 13:43:17.306673','2025-04-03 13:43:17.306673',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,0,'TRADITIONAL DANCE','3. Traditional Dance Performance: Experience the energy and excitement of traditional African dance performances in Kenya, Tanzania, or Uganda.\n    - Book with Mugga Tours: Watch talented local dancers perform traditional routines, accompanied by lively music and colorful costumes.\n    - Exciting fact: Traditional African dance is an important part of cultural heritage, often telling stories and conveying messages.','FULL DAY',1.00,'Mon,Tue,Wed,Thur,Fri,Sat,Sun','https://res.cloudinary.com/dgjtaqrhg/image/upload/v1743687775/MUGGA_Wallpaper_PNG_5_vz13zk.png',1,20,'activity'),(23,'2025-04-03 13:46:34.857886','2025-04-03 13:46:34.857886',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,0,'SNORKELING ','1. Snorkeling or Scuba Diving: Explore the stunning coral reefs and marine life of the Indian Ocean in Tanzania or Kenya.\n    - Book with Mugga Tours: Discover the incredible diversity of marine life, including colorful fish, sea turtles, and coral.\n    - Exciting fact: The coral reefs off the coast of Tanzania and Kenya are some of the most pristine and diverse in the world.','FULL DAY',1.00,'Mon,Tue,Wed,Thur,Fri,Sat,Sun','https://res.cloudinary.com/dgjtaqrhg/image/upload/v1743687890/wp5623932-snorkeling-hd-wallpapers_j11gkf.jpg',1,20,'activity'),(24,'2025-04-03 13:47:31.322073','2025-04-03 13:47:31.322073',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,0,'FISHING','2. Fishing: Try your hand at deep-sea fishing or freshwater fishing in Kenya\'s Lake Victoria or Tanzania\'s Lake Tanganyika.\n    - Book with Mugga Tours: Join experienced fishing guides for a day of fishing, with the chance to catch a variety of species.\n    - Exciting fact: Lake Victoria is home to over 200 species of fish, including the iconic Nile perch.','FULL DAY',1.00,'Mon,Tue,Wed,Thur,Fri,Sat,Sun','https://res.cloudinary.com/dgjtaqrhg/image/upload/v1743688046/wp15007445-kayak-fishing-wallpapers_uqxd8a.webp',1,20,'activity'),(25,'2025-04-03 13:54:08.458899','2025-04-03 13:54:08.458899',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,0,'BOAT CRUISE','3. Boat Cruises: Relax on a sunset cruise or explore the coastline of Kenya or Tanzania by boat.\n    - Book with Mugga Tours: Enjoy stunning views of the coastline, marine life, and surrounding landscape while cruising on a comfortable boat.\n    - Exciting fact: A boat cruise is a great way to spot dolphins, whales, and other marine life in their natural habitat.','FULL DAY',1.00,'Mon,Tue,Wed,Thur,Fri,Sat,Sun','https://res.cloudinary.com/dgjtaqrhg/image/u